\f2\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \strokec2 In addition to textual remediation, the website architecture must feature mandatory structural disclosures to satisfy licensing transparency. These elements are optimally placed in a global footer that propagates across every indexed page. This includes the legal name, the trading name, the Australian Business Number, and the precise licensing statement: "NC Finance (Credit Representative Number) is authorised under Australian Credit Licence 389328".
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 4
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2  The site must also ensure that any interest rates published are accompanied by their corresponding comparison rates and the necessary legislative warnings detailing what the comparison rate does and does not include.
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 4
\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf2 \nosupersub \strokec2  Furthermore, any client testimonials utilized for social proof must be stripped of identifying data beyond the client's first name and suburb to prevent privacy breaches.
\fs19\fsmilli9600 \cf4 \super \strokec4 4
